# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# .trivyignore — Trivy CVE Ignore List
# Customer Intelligence Platform
#
# Format: one CVE/GHSA ID per line. Comments start with #.
# Reference: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/
#
# PURPOSE
# ───────
# Add CVE IDs here ONLY after security triage confirms one of:
#   1. The CVE is not exploitable in this deployment context
#   2. No fix version is available AND the risk is formally accepted
#   3. The finding is a confirmed false positive
#
# REQUIRED COMMENT FORMAT FOR EACH ENTRY
# ───────────────────────────────────────
# CVE-YYYY-NNNNN
# Package: <package-name> <version>
# Severity: CRITICAL|HIGH|MEDIUM|LOW
# Reason: <one-sentence triage justification>
# Attack vector not applicable because: <why this doesn't apply>
# Accepted by: <name>, <date>
# Review by: <date + 90 days>
#
# QUARTERLY REVIEW
# ────────────────
# Review all entries every 90 days or when Trivy reports a fix is available.
# Remove entries when a patched base image or package version is available.
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ─── Base image: python:3.11-slim (Debian bookworm) ──────────────────────────
# The following are commonly marked WILL_NOT_FIX or LOW priority by Debian.
# Un-comment and add specific CVE IDs after your first trivy scan and triage.
# Always include the full comment block above when activating an entry.

# Example — replace with real CVE after triage:
# CVE-2010-4756
# Package: libc6 2.36-9+deb12u9
# Severity: LOW
# Reason: glibc glob(3) DoS via crafted pattern; no local shell access in production
# Attack vector not applicable because: EKS pods run as non-root (uid=1000),
#   no interactive shell, no attacker-controlled filesystem paths in glob calls
# Accepted by: platform-security-team, 2026-02-25
# Review by: 2026-05-25

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# End of .trivyignore
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
